<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a533ae0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s6006"><num value="6006">§ 6006.</num><heading> “Approved bicycle helmet” defined</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter, the term “approved bicycle helmet” means a bicycle helmet that meets—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a533ae1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s6006/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> any interim standard described in <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s6004/b">section 6004(b) of this title</ref>, pending establishment of a final standard under <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s6004/c">section 6004(c) of this title</ref>; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a533ae2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s6006/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the final standard, once it is established under <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s6004/c">section 6004(c) of this title</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a533ae3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/267/tII/s207">Pub. L. 103–267, title II, § 207</ref>, <date date="1994-06-16">June 16, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/728">108 Stat. 728</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
